  "prompt": "Is there a database with all nutritional information?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several comprehensive databases that provide nutritional information for a wide variety of foods. Some of the most well-known include:\n\n1. **USDA FoodData Central**: Managed by the United States Department of Agriculture, this database includes detailed nutritional information on thousands of food items, including raw, cooked, and processed foods.\n\n2. **NutritionData**: This website offers detailed nutritional profiles for a wide range of foods, including macronutrients, micronutrients, and caloric content.\n\n3. **MyFitnessPal**: This popular app and website provide nutritional information on a vast array of foods, including user-submitted data for restaurant meals and packaged foods.\n\n4. **Cronometer**: Similar to MyFitnessPal, Cronometer offers detailed nutritional information and allows users to track their dietary intake.\n\n5. **Food Standards Australia New Zealand (FSANZ) NUTTAB**: This is another comprehensive food composition database, providing detailed nutritional data for foods available in Australia and New Zealand.\n\nThese databases are valuable resources for anyone looking to manage their diet, conduct nutritional research, or simply learn more about the nutritional content of the foods they consume.",
